        <span class="layer-desc">3+ sessions/week · The stimulus</span>
      </div>
      <div class="foundation-layer second">
        <span class="layer-name">2. Adequate Daily Protein (100g+)</span>
        <span class="layer-desc">The raw material · Non-negotiable</span>
      </div>
      <div class="foundation-layer top">
        <span class="layer-name">3. Everything Else</span>
        <span class="layer-desc">Supplements · Peptides · Optimization</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Most men doing the research on peptides are at step 3 before they've locked in steps 1 and 2. That's not their fault — step 3 is what gets marketed. Steps 1 and 2 are boring. Nobody's running ads for eating chicken breast and doing squats consistently.</p>

    <h2>What Happens When You Optimize Without a Foundation</h2>

